{
  "texts": [
    "Our next result establishes the impact of filter bubbles on voter polarization.",
    "We refer to the individuals who are at the median among the left-leaning and the right-leaning voters, respectively (those that the midpoints between 0 and 1/2, and between 1/2 and 1, or mathematically, H-1 (1/4) and H-1 (3/4))",
    "as the left median and the right median.",
    "Proposition 4.3.",
    "There exist 0 < r 1 < r 2 < r P < 1 such that an article with reliability r ∈ (r 1, r 2) leads to voter polarization in the sense that HF B ≻ HC, but the left and the right medians remain identical under both belief distributions, i.e., H-1"
  ]
}